{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Amdyy4NXsZdoqbo3WLvwNX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Code Review — Iteration 25 (Vocabulary Corroboration)\n     2→\n     3→## Review Scope\n     4→\n     5→**Target:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` + `lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts`\n     6→**Changes:** +85 lines in title-extractor.ts, +93 lines in tests (after review fixes applied)\n     7→**Focus:** Architecture, code quality, performance, testing — compared against `improvement-plan.md`\n     8→\n     9→## Executive Summary\n    10→\n    11→The iteration adds **vocabulary corroboration** to filter orphaned OCR artifacts from multi-title assembly. The fix is well-targeted — it solves the FINNISH FLATBREADS failure without regressions. The implementation follows the improvement plan closely, with one smart deviation (≥3 alpha chars instead of ≥4 raw chars for content words).\n    12→\n    13→**Review fixes applied:**\n    14→1. Extracted duplicated corroboration logic into `passesCorroboration()` helper\n    15→2. Fixed test indentation (off by 2 spaces in all 3 new test cases)\n    16→\n    17→## Quality Metrics\n    18→\n    19→| Aspect | Score | Notes |\n    20→|---|---|---|\n    21→| Architecture | 8/10 | Clean integration at two well-chosen points; dual application (pre-filter + post-filter) is defense-in-depth, not redundancy |\n    22→| Code Quality | 8/10 | After DRY fix — `passesCorroboration` eliminates 3x duplication of threshold logic |\n    23→| Performance | 9/10 | O(candidates × words × lines) ≈ ~200 string ops — negligible vs. embedding cost |\n    24→| Testing | 8/10 | Three focused test cases covering the key scenarios; good use of realistic document structure |\n    25→\n    26→## Issues Found and Fixed\n    27→\n    28→### 1. DRY Violation — Duplicated Threshold Logic (MEDIUM)\n    29→\n    30→**Before:** Content-word extraction + threshold calculation was copy-pasted in 3 places:\n    31→- `corroborationScore()` (score computation only)\n    32→- Pre-filter block (~line 1125) — inline threshold decision\n    33→- Post-filter block (~line 1316) — inline threshold decision\n    34→\n    35→**Fix:** Extracted `passesCorroboration(text, position, allLines): boolean` that encapsulates both the score computation and threshold decision. Both call sites now use the helper.\n    36→\n    37→### 2. Test Indentation (LOW)\n    38→\n    39→**Before:** The 3 new test cases inside `describe(\"corroboration\")` had bodies indented at 4 spaces instead of 6 (2nd and 3rd `it()` blocks were at 2 spaces instead of 4).\n    40→\n    41→**Fix:** Corrected all indentation to be consistent with the rest of the test file.\n    42→\n    43→## Design Analysis\n    44→\n    45→### Dual corroboration (pre-filter + post-filter) — Intentional and correct\n    46→\n    47→The corroboration check runs at two distinct points:\n    48→\n    49→1. **Pre-filter** (before threshold computation): Removes artifacts from `scoredForThreshold` so they don't inflate the threshold via early-position bonus. Safety: only removes if ≥2 ALL_CAPS candidates remain.\n    50→\n    51→2. **Post-filter** (in multi-title assembly): Removes artifacts from the final `selected` set. Safety: falls back to unfiltered set if <2 candidates survive.\n    52→\n    53→These serve different purposes — the pre-filter affects which candidates survive threshold filtering, while the post-filter affects the final output. If the pre-filter's safety check prevents removal (e.g., only 2 ALL_CAPS total, one is artifact), the post-filter catches it.\n    54→\n    55→### Content word threshold: ≥3 alpha chars (deviation from plan)\n    56→\n    57→The plan specified `w.length >= 4` (raw length). The implementation uses `w.replace(/[^a-zA-ZÀ-ÿ]/g, \"\").length >= 3` (alpha-only length after stripping punctuation). This is a better choice:\n    58→\n    59→- Handles punctuation-rich OCR output (e.g., \"DAT\" → 3 alpha chars, included as content word)\n    60→- \"DAT\" with raw length 3 would be excluded by the plan's ≥4 threshold, making corroboration trivially pass — the fix wouldn't work\n    61→- Unicode-aware via `À-ÿ` range (important for Polish recipes)\n    62→\n    63→## Strengths to Preserve\n    64→\n    65→- **Minimal, targeted fix** — only touches the multi-title path, single-title pages completely unaffected\n    66→- **Good safety guards** — both pre-filter and post-filter have \"don't remove all candidates\" fallbacks\n    67→- **Clear comments** explaining the purpose of each corroboration step\n    68→- **Test cases match real failure mode** — the artifact test uses realistic garbled OCR preamble\n    69→\n    70→## Verification Results\n    71→\n    72→- **Unit tests:** 36/36 passing\n    73→- **Type check:** Clean\n    74→- **CLI (11 real files):** All correct, including the previously-failing FINNISH FLATBREADS case\n    75→- **No regressions**\n    76→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"85fd2af6-6c55-4da1-a228-07fff6134a1a","uuid":"7ad382d2-c590-46a5-9320-b8d9b3937712","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/25-2331e30/review.md","content":"# Code Review — Iteration 25 (Vocabulary Corroboration)\n\n## Review Scope\n\n**Target:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` + `lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts`\n**Changes:** +85 lines in title-extractor.ts, +93 lines in tests (after review fixes applied)\n**Focus:** Architecture, code quality, performance, testing — compared against `improvement-plan.md`\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThe iteration adds **vocabulary corroboration** to filter orphaned OCR artifacts from multi-title assembly. The fix is well-targeted — it solves the FINNISH FLATBREADS failure without regressions. The implementation follows the improvement plan closely, with one smart deviation (≥3 alpha chars instead of ≥4 raw chars for content words).\n\n**Review fixes applied:**\n1. Extracted duplicated corroboration logic into `passesCorroboration()` helper\n2. Fixed test indentation (off by 2 spaces in all 3 new test cases)\n\n## Quality Metrics\n\n| Aspect | Score | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Architecture | 8/10 | Clean integration at two well-chosen points; dual application (pre-filter + post-filter) is defense-in-depth, not redundancy |\n| Code Quality | 8/10 | After DRY fix — `passesCorroboration` eliminates 3x duplication of threshold logic |\n| Performance | 9/10 | O(candidates × words × lines) ≈ ~200 string ops — negligible vs. embedding cost |\n| Testing | 8/10 | Three focused test cases covering the key scenarios; good use of realistic document structure |\n\n## Issues Found and Fixed\n\n### 1. DRY Violation — Duplicated Threshold Logic (MEDIUM)\n\n**Before:** Content-word extraction + threshold calculation was copy-pasted in 3 places:\n- `corroborationScore()` (score computation only)\n- Pre-filter block (~line 1125) — inline threshold decision\n- Post-filter block (~line 1316) — inline threshold decision\n\n**Fix:** Extracted `passesCorroboration(text, position, allLines): boolean` that encapsulates both the score computation and threshold decision. Both call sites now use the helper.\n\n### 2. Test Indentation (LOW)\n\n**Before:** The 3 new test cases inside `describe(\"corroboration\")` had bodies indented at 4 spaces instead of 6 (2nd and 3rd `it()` blocks were at 2 spaces instead of 4).\n\n**Fix:** Corrected all indentation to be consistent with the rest of the test file.\n\n## Design Analysis\n\n### Dual corroboration (pre-filter + post-filter) — Intentional and correct\n\nThe corroboration check runs at two distinct points:\n\n1. **Pre-filter** (before threshold computation): Removes artifacts from `scoredForThreshold` so they don't inflate the threshold via early-position bonus. Safety: only removes if ≥2 ALL_CAPS candidates remain.\n\n2. **Post-filter** (in multi-title assembly): Removes artifacts from the final `selected` set. Safety: falls back to unfiltered set if <2 candidates survive.\n\nThese serve different purposes — the pre-filter affects which candidates survive threshold filtering, while the post-filter affects the final output. If the pre-filter's safety check prevents removal (e.g., only 2 ALL_CAPS total, one is artifact), the post-filter catches it.\n\n### Content word threshold: ≥3 alpha chars (deviation from plan)\n\nThe plan specified `w.length >= 4` (raw length). The implementation uses `w.replace(/[^a-zA-ZÀ-ÿ]/g, \"\").length >= 3` (alpha-only length after stripping punctuation). This is a better choice:\n\n- Handles punctuation-rich OCR output (e.g., \"DAT\" → 3 alpha chars, included as content word)\n- \"DAT\" with raw length 3 would be excluded by the plan's ≥4 threshold, making corroboration trivially pass — the fix wouldn't work\n- Unicode-aware via `À-ÿ` range (important for Polish recipes)\n\n## Strengths to Preserve\n\n- **Minimal, targeted fix** — only touches the multi-title path, single-title pages completely unaffected\n- **Good safety guards** — both pre-filter and post-filter have \"don't remove all candidates\" fallbacks\n- **Clear comments** explaining the purpose of each corroboration step\n- **Test cases match real failure mode** — the artifact test uses realistic garbled OCR preamble\n\n## Verification Results\n\n- **Unit tests:** 36/36 passing\n- **Type check:** Clean\n- **CLI (11 real files):** All correct, including the previously-failing FINNISH FLATBREADS case\n- **No regressions**\n","numLines":76,"startLine":1,"totalLines":76}}}
